    <section class="hero-section">
        <div class="container text-center">
            <h1 class="section-title">JALAPATIH VI</h1>
            <p class="text-muted fs-5 mb-0">The Peak of Maritime Innovation</p>
            
            <div class="hud-image-wrapper">
                <div class="hud-corner hud-top-left"></div>
                <div class="hud-corner hud-top-right"></div>
                <div class="hud-corner hud-bottom-left"></div>
                <div class="hud-corner hud-bottom-right"></div>
                <img src="/assets/jp6 render livery.png" alt="Jalapatih VI" class="main-boat-img">
            </div>

            <p class="mx-auto text-light mb-5" style="max-width: 800px; font-size: 1.1rem;">
                Our latest flagship vessel. Engineered for maximum efficiency and speed, integrating active hydrofoil control systems for precise altitude and orientation to maintain optimal stability during flight.
            </p>

            <div class="row g-4 justify-content-center px-lg-5">
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Breadth</p><p class="spec-value">1.7 m</p></div></div>
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Depth</p><p class="spec-value">0.5 m</p></div></div>
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Draught</p><p class="spec-value">0.15 m</p></div></div>
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Length Overall</p><p class="spec-value">5.1 m</p></div></div>
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Top Speed</p><p class="spec-value">30 Km/h</p></div></div>
                <div class="col-6 col-md-4"><div class="spec-card"><p class="spec-label">Endurance</p><p class="spec-value">58 Mins</p></div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="legacy-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title mb-5 pb-4">OUR LEGACY</h2>

            <div class="legacy-row">
                <div class="legacy-img-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/jp5wew.png" alt="Jalapatih V" class="legacy-img">
                </div>
                <div class="legacy-text">
                    <h3 class="legacy-name">JALAPATIH V</h3>
                    <p class="legacy-desc">Jalapatih V is lighter. The use of carbon material with the vacuum infusion method makes the boat 50% lighter than its predecessor. Jalapatih V used a planing hull that can help the hydrofoil in providing an angle of attack.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legacy-row">
                <div class="legacy-img-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/jp4.png" alt="Jalapatih IV" class="legacy-img">
                </div>
                <div class="legacy-text">
                    <h3 class="legacy-name">JALAPATIH IV</h3>
                    <p class="legacy-desc">Jalapatih IV was the first hydrofoil solar boat in Indonesia. Hydrofoil technology increased the boat's speed and efficiency.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legacy-row">
                <div class="legacy-img-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/jp3.png" alt="Jalapatih III" class="legacy-img">
                </div>
                <div class="legacy-text">
                    <h3 class="legacy-name">JALAPATIH III</h3>
                    <p class="legacy-desc">Jalapatih III had a longer endurance and it used a flexible solar panel to reduce the boat’s weight. It was equipped with electrical instruments that sent the boat’s technical information. Jalapatih III won as 3rd Top Speed Category on Solar Sport One.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legacy-row">
                <div class="legacy-img-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/jp2.png" alt="Jalapatih II" class="legacy-img">
                </div>
                <div class="legacy-text">
                    <h3 class="legacy-name">JALAPATIH II</h3>
                    <p class="legacy-desc">Jalapatih II was designed to improve the boat’s stability. Jalapatih II use carbon fiber as its main material. Therefore, it provided a strong but light body. Jalapatih II won 2nd Runner Up in Asia Dutch Solar Challenge 2016.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legacy-row">
                <div class="legacy-img-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/jp1.png" alt="Jalapatih I" class="legacy-img">
                </div>
                <div class="legacy-text">
                    <h3 class="legacy-name">JALAPATIH I</h3>
                    <p class="legacy-desc">Jalapatih I was designed to have a dynamic boat hull and good stability as a fin stabiliser attached to the body. Jalapatih I competed in The Dong Solar Energy Challenge 2014, became the first ever representation solar boat in ASEAN.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            </div>
    </section>

